Description: FS is a used Collector’s Edition ‘97 Fender Stratocaster Limited run. This particular guitar is # 1725 of 1997. This guitar is essentially a limited edition run of the ‘62 reissue with Texas Special Single coils and gold hardware, but much less common. This is your chance to own a crunchy, blues machine reminiscent of the SRV style Strats. This guitar shows signs of play wear including a paint chip low on the face of the body, picking damage above the strings (in the direction of a strum), a paint chip low on the rear of the body, and back of the neck damage close to the head. There are various lift scratches in the paint visible in the right light. The first owner also removed a chunk of the pick guard to expose the truss rod adjustment. A replacement pick guard can be picked up from Fender if you wanted to. This guitar is a sweet player, but I’m moving and need to reduce the collection. The guitar comes with the original case(including lock keys), paperwork, trem bar, and trem cover.
